body:
Hi,
I have an App where i use a model popup page with a transparent background, i have a skcanvasview on the bottom of that page and I was trying to apply a blur  with skmaskfilter, but that didnt work. I did it like this:
```csharp
SKMaskFilter mask = SKMaskFilter.CreateBlur(SKBlurStyle.Normal, 50);
                SKPaint paint = new SKPaint() {
                    Color = new SKColor(0, 0, 0, 200),
                    MaskFilter = mask,
 };
canvas.DrawPaint(paint);
```

Then i thought that I can snapshot the background turn it into a bitmap and blur it using skimagefilter, but that doesnt work eithei, the bitmap is not null but it doesnt display the image on background.

```csharp
public async void OnPaint(object sender, SKPaintSurfaceEventArgs e) {
    try {
        SKSurface surface = e.Surface;
        SKCanvas canvas = surface.Canvas;
        var data = surface.Snapshot().Encode(SKEncodedImageFormat.Png, 80);
        SKBitmap bitmap = SKBitmap.Decode(data, new SKImageInfo(e.Info.Width, e.Info.Height));

        SKMaskFilter mask = SKMaskFilter.CreateBlur(SKBlurStyle.Normal, 50);
        SKImageFilter ImageFilter = SKImageFilter.CreateBlur(5, 5);
        SKPaint paint = new SKPaint() {
            ImageFilter = ImageFilter,
            Color = new SKColor(0, 0, 0, 200),
            MaskFilter = mask,
        };
        canvas.DrawRect(new SKRect(0, 0, e.Info.Width, e.Info.Height), paint);
        SKPaint paint1 = new SKPaint() {
            Color = SKColors.Green,
        };
        if (bitmap != null) {
            canvas.DrawBitmap(bitmap, new SKPoint(0, 0), paint);
            Console.WriteLine("Usou a imagem.");
        }
        else {
            canvas.DrawPaint(paint1);
            Console.WriteLine("Não usou a imagem.");
        }
    }
    catch (Exception ex) {
        await DisplayAlert("erro canvas", ex.Message, "ok");
    }
}
```
I am using a popup page from https://github.com/rotorgames/Rg.Plugins.Popup, all i want to do is blur the background, if somebody has ever faced an issue like this please help me.
